<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="do-aux-v">do <strong><em>aux v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /də:;du:/    美 /də:;du/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.****</h4>
<ul>
<li>构成疑问句、否定句或倒装句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Didn’t he sing well?
难道他唱得不好吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I don’t care what she thinks.
我不在乎她想什么。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Only then did he realize that he was wrong.
直到那时他才意识到自己错了。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>用于加强语气，发强音：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>For the happiness of your family, do obey traffic rules.
为了您的家庭幸福,请务必遵守交通规则。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He does speak well.
他确实讲得不错。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>代替动词 (词组)，以免重复：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— May I come round in the morning?
我上午来行吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Yes, please do.
行，来吧。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My secretary worked later than I did at the office.
秘书下班比我晚。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>It doesn’t matter if they want to come to your party, <strong><em>_</em></strong>_?   （2011 上海）<br />
A.doesn’t it<br />
B.does it<br />
C.don’t they<br />
D.do they  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. B  </p></div>